# Compodoc Integration in Storybook 10 for Angular

## Configuration in angular.json

To set up Compodoc, add these options to both `storybook` and `build-storybook` builders:

```json
{
  "projects": {
    "your-project": {
      "architect": {
        "storybook": {
          "builder": "@storybook/angular:start-storybook",
          "options": {
            "compodoc": true,
            "compodocArgs": [
              "-e",
              "json",
              "-d",
              "."
            ]
          }
        },
        "build-storybook": {
          "builder": "@storybook/angular:build-storybook",
          "options": {
            "compodoc": true,
            "compodocArgs": [
              "-e",
              "json",
              "-d",
              "."
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## setCompodocJson API

The current recommended approach uses: `"import { setCompodocJson } from '@storybook/addon-docs/angular'"`

In your `.storybook/preview.ts`:

```typescript
import { setCompodocJson } from '@storybook/addon-docs/angular';
import docJson from '../documentation.json';
setCompodocJson(docJson);
```

## Key Changes in Storybook 10

The documentation notes that "compodoc is now built into @storybook/angular; you don't have to call it explicitly." Previously, developers needed separate `docs:json` npm scripts. The builder now handles Compodoc execution automatically.

## Documentation Setup

Add JSDoc comments above `@Inputs` and `@Outputs` in your Angular components, as these directly map to Storybook's control interface.

