# Enabling Autodocs in Storybook 10

## Required Addon

The `@storybook/addon-docs` addon is required. Ensure it's listed in your `.storybook/main.ts`:

```typescript
const config: StorybookConfig = {
  framework: '@storybook/your-framework',
  stories: ['../src/**/*.mdx', '../src/**/*.stories.@(js|jsx|mjs|ts|tsx)'],
  addons: ['@storybook/addon-docs'],
};

export default config;
```

## Main.ts Configuration

You can optionally customize documentation behavior using the `docs` option:

```typescript
const config: StorybookConfig = {
  framework: '@storybook/your-framework',
  addons: ['@storybook/addon-docs'],
  docs: {
    defaultName: 'Documentation', // Renames the docs page
    docsMode: true, // Shows only documentation in sidebar
  },
};

export default config;
```

## Enable Autodocs via Tags

Enable automatic documentation globally in `.storybook/preview.ts`:

```typescript
const preview: Preview = {
  tags: ['autodocs'],
};

export default preview;
```

## Story Meta Configuration

Enable autodocs per-component in your story file:

```typescript
const meta = {
  component: Button,
  tags: ['autodocs'], // Generates docs for this component
} satisfies Meta<typeof Button>;

export default meta;
```

To disable for specific components, use `tags: ['!autodocs']`.

