## Task

> Set up Compodoc with Storybook in this Nx Angular library. Add a sample input and a sample output to our component using the input() and output() signal functions. The Docs tab should render JSDoc descriptions for the component, the input, and the output.

## Orientation Findings

1. `@storybook/angular@10.3.5` and `storybook@10.3.5` are installed; `@storybook/addon-docs` is NOT installed; `@compodoc/compodoc` is NOT installed.
2. Angular is at `~21.2.0`, `@nx/storybook@22.6.5`, `@nx/angular@22.6.5`.
3. The library has one component `NgxSmartComponents` (no inputs/outputs yet) at `packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.ts`.
4. `.storybook/main.ts` has `addons: []` (empty) — no docs addon configured.
5. `project.json` storybook targets have `"compodoc": false` and no `compodocArgs`.
6. `preview.ts` is effectively empty (1 line, no content).
7. In Storybook 10, `@storybook/addon-essentials` was removed; actions/controls/viewport moved into core. `@storybook/addon-docs` was NOT merged into core — it still requires a separate install and explicit `addons` entry.
8. `setCompodocJson` is NOT exported anywhere in the installed `@storybook/angular@10.3.5` package. The internal `getCompodocJson()` reads from `global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__`. The `@storybook/global` package is installed and exports `global`.
9. `@storybook/addon-docs/angular` subpath does NOT exist in the installed packages. Whether it exists after installing `@storybook/addon-docs` is unverified.
10. Signal `input()` and `output()` support was added in Compodoc 1.1.27 (properly classified as Inputs/Outputs, not Properties). Compodoc 1.2.1 is the current version.
11. The `@storybook/angular` builder looks for `tsconfig.doc.json` starting from `options.configDir` (`.storybook/`); if not found, falls back to the regular tsConfig.
12. The builder defaults to outputting `documentation.json` to the workspace root when no `-d` flag in `compodocArgs`. With `-d packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook`, import in `preview.ts` is simply `./documentation.json`.
13. Autodocs in Storybook 10 requires: (a) `@storybook/addon-docs` in addons, (b) either `tags: ['autodocs']` in the story meta or globally in `preview.ts`.

